	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320192_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Y.L., 18 years old</p>
			<p>Cutter and stitcher of shoe-leather</p>
			<p>Z.L., 21 years old</p>
			<p>Carpenter</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">Brothers</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów Mazowiecka</placeName></p>
			<p>Details about the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">mass massacre</term></p>
			<p>in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów Mazowiecka</placeName></p>
			<p>Protocol No. 192</p>
			<p>(compiled on <date when="1940-02-18">February 18, 1940</date>)</p>
			<p>We can give the following details about the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">mass
					massacre</term> of Jews in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów Mazowiecka</placeName>
					(<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Great Ostrów</placeName>).</p>

			<p>It was Thursday, <date when="1939-11-09">November 9, 1939</date>. On this day, 561 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">Jews died</term>.</p>

			<p>We ourselves talked to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">perished</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_modrykamyen_yosl">Yosl Modrykamyen</persName>, who was also <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term> on this very day (he was approximately
				35 years old). <persName ref="#ehri_et_modrykamyen_yosl">Yosl Modrykamyen</persName>’s <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">wife</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">died</term> as well. Only his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> was able to save herself.</p>

			<p>We also talked with a Jew, who was in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName> on the
				day of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">massacre</term> and survived owing to the
				fact that he was wearing a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term> [peaked]
				cap, <q>a matsheyuvke</q>, <note type="gloss">a kind of cap with a visor</note> and he was shaved and generally looked like a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term>.</p>

			<p>They both related that the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> themselves placarded posters on the streets
				announcing that the Jews of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">died</term> in accordance with a verdict of a <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">court</term>.</p>

			<p><pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320192_02.jpg"/> The calamity happened under the following circumstances:</p>

			<p>One side of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Rinek</placeName> caught fire (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Rinek</placeName> the street is called where once there was a market;
				officially: <q><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Square of the Duchess Anna
						</placeName><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Mazowiecka</placeName></q>). Only Jewish
				houses are located there like the house of <persName ref="#ehri_et_teytel">Teytel</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_likhtnshteyn"
					>Likhtnshteyn</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kronenberg">Kronenberg</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_bromberg"
					>Bromberg</persName> and of others. There were stores for textiles, haberdasheries, groceries and also a candy store. It was
				almost the main street.</p>

			<p>We presume that the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> themselves set the houses on fire. The houses burnt a
				whole night.</p>

			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> later implied that the Jews set the fire. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> promised the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Poles</term> 25 Złoty
				per head when they turn over Jews, and the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Poles</term> constantly dragged Jews to the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">city hall</placeName> where the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> station was located. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term> mob together with the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>
				dragged the Jews out of the houses. Everyone was dragged out, also old people, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>.</p>

			<p>From the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">city hall</placeName> the Jews were led to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Warsaw Road</placeName>, after <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Starastve Street</placeName>, near the woods of the former <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term> commander where once there was a summer house. This is located one and a half
				kilometres away from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów Mazowiecka</placeName>.</p>

			<p>There, 561 Jews were gathered, and the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> ordered the Jews to dig out <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1321" type="subject">pits</term>. And the Jews had to lay themselves into
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1321" type="subject">pits</term>. Parents had to throw their own
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1321" type="subject">pits</term>, and with rifles and revolvers all Jews
				were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot to death</term>.</p>

			<p><pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320192_03.jpg"/> The remaining Jews, who were caught after the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">execution</term> [had taken place], were led into the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> as well as into the ice cellar of
				the brewery of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brothers</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_teytel">Teytel</persName>.</p>

			<p>Since <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName> is less than 2 kilometres away from the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviet</term> border, the majority of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName>’s inhabitants ran away to the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Russian</term> side. Roughly 15 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term> remained who haven’t had the
				opportunity to leave because of the older people.</p>

			<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject">refugees</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html"
					>Łódź</placeName> and other cities arrived. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject"
					>refugees</term> weren’t able to cross the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Russian</term> border anymore which was
				already closed and they returned to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName> and
				there they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">died</term>.</p>

			<p>Among the victims from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów Mazowiecka</placeName>, the
				following names are known:</p>

			<p>1–2) Two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughters</term> of <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_knorpel">Knorpel</persName> (the owner of a vinegar <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-890" type="subject">factory</term> and the chairman of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish community</term>); both <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term> were over 20 years old. Their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term>, the chairman of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish community</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_knorpel">Knorpel</persName>, survived because of a large sum of money thanks to which <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christians</term> took him <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">across the border</term>.</p>

			<p>3–4) <persName ref="#ehri_et_veydenboym_dvoyre">Dvoyre Veydenboym</persName>, from Lipsker’s home, a midwife, around 35 to 40 years
				old; also her little <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">daughter</term>, 7 years of
				age, studying in a <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-878" type="subject">Tarbut school</term></q>.</p>

			<p>(<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christians</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">child</term>. But then <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Poles</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-200" type="subject">denounced</term> these <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christians</term> to the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and the latter <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot</term> the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">child</term> in front of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>. Her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term>, engineer <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_veydenboym">Veydenboym</persName>, is in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530772/bialystok.html"
					>Białystok</placeName>.)</p>

			<pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320192_4.jpg"/>

			<p>5)<persName ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_rivke">Rivke Lipsker</persName>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sister</term> of <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_veydenboym_dvoyre">Dvoyre Veydenboym</persName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_rivke">Rivke Lipsker</persName> was
				approximately 35 years old. She was a hotel owner, a widow.</p>

			<p>6)<persName ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_perl">Perl</persName>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">daughter</term> of <persName ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_rivke">Rivke Lipsker</persName>, roughly 20 years old, a
				domestic worker, unmarried.</p>

			<p>(<persName ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_rivke">Rivke Lipsker</persName>’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">son</term>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_vevl">Velvl</persName>, who was serving in the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">army</term>, is located in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530772/bialystok.html">Białystok</placeName> now.)</p>

			<p>A mass of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject">refugees</term> were taken out of <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_lipsker_rivke">Rivke Lipsker</persName>’s hotel and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term>.</p>

			<p>7)<persName ref="#ehri_et_volmark_shelke">Volmark Shelke</persName>, in his fifties, a coachman.</p>

			<p>On the day of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">massacre</term>, he <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> on the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-750" type="subject">Jewish cemetery</term>. Then, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> came there and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">chopped off his head</term> with a sword. His <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">son</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_volmark_mendl">Mendl Volmark</persName>, who had left <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/762850/ostrow-mazowiecka.html">Ostrów</placeName> long before, is in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530772/bialystok.html">Białystok</placeName> now.</p>

			<p>The Jew, who survived thanks to his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term>
				appearance, told us that he remembers well the faces of some <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Poles</term>, who informed the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> where Jews were living and dragged them out and turned them over to the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> for money. The Jew will not rest and testify whenever it will be
				possible.</p>

			<p>Our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> survived miraculously. A bomb
				entered the house but he was not harmed.</p>

			<p>Signed: Y.R.</p>

